Now, bear in mind I am not saying that they can make a deal appear to be one thing so that they can take advantage of taxes, the tax consequences when actually it is something else. It is the substance and not the form which governs. For example, I couldn\rquote t, when I pay my rent to my landlord, in the hypothetical I just suggested to you, I can\rquote t write the check to interest and he can\rquote t, to accommodate me, say, \u8220\'3fWell, this is interest.\u8221\'3f When he receives my money and gives me a receipt he can\rquote t say interest, and I can\rquote t say interest if, in fact, I am paying him rent. We can\rquote t make the form appear to be one thing if the substance is something else.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
